radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated to 9 mm, is fluid filled, and has periappendiceal stranding. Normal visualized heart, clear lung bases, normal liver, gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, kidneys, gastrointestinal tract, bladder, and prostate gland. No extraluminal gas or periappendiceal collection, no retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy, and no abdominal wall hernia.
